Final Fantasy Tactics<br>
FF7<br>
FF10<br>
<br>
I too also thought that Hoshigami was going to be very cool. Hell, I even preordered it. But when I actually sat down and played it, it just sucked majorly. I mean, I appreciate the level of difficulty, but I hate working really hard on one character only to have them die and never come back. No Phoenix Downs here people, just the cold hard embrace of death.<br>
<br>
And then there's the magic system. Atlus thought they would be really cool if they had magic contained in these coins, and the first thing that popped into my head was &quot;MATERIA!&quot; (This also fooled me into getting the game.)<br>
<br>
Well, little did I know that the MP that you spend casting spells doesn't come from your characters, but from the coins itself. Why on earth would the coins contain MP, but not you?<br>
So in battle you can only use 1 spell per coin, and then that's about it. Plus, you dont' see any enemies use coins either - I guess they know better.<br>
<br>
The leveling system in the game just blows as well. Instead of running over previous battle areas like in Tactics, you have a leveling tower instead in Hoshigami. A very long, and boring, leveling tower.<br>
<br>
Deep down inside, I feel very sorry not for Atlus, but for the artists who spent their dedicated time into making the very good artwork for such a horrible game. *sigh*<br>
<br>
On other words, has anyone ever ran into the 10 ninja battle, or the 10 monk battle in Tactics? It's usually over the Mendalia Plains, that this very rare battle takes place. It's frustratingly difficult, and fun at the same time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>====================<br>
